; Deep linear derivation chain over a @differential base fact. The driver
; feeds a descending next-chain N -> N-1 -> ... -> 0 and the single base
; fact base(N), so reach(k) has exactly one derivation of depth N - k and
; the deepest row reach(0) has the numerically smallest key. Retracting
; base(N) marks the whole chain unknown, and the recheck resolves rows in
; ascending key order, so the first checker call on reach(0) recurses
; through all N unresolved predecessors -- the maximum-recursion-depth
; shape for the top-down checker machinery. The driver's chain depth is
; chosen empirically to pass in today's debug build with stack headroom
; to spare (see kChainDepth in the driver); the Stage 3 acceptance gate
; raises it to 100000 in constant stack.
#message base(u64 X) @differential.
#message next(u64 From, u64 To).

#local reach(X).

#query reach_out(free u64 X).

reach(X) : base(X).
reach(Y) : reach(X), next(X, Y).

reach_out(X) : reach(X).
